{"id":"119","name":"bright-early-not-so-fast-edition","title":"Bright &amp; Early: Not So Fast Edition","author":"Christy Frink","date":"2008-05-20T09:00:00-05:00","tags":["bonnaroo","fuse tv","glencliff high school","kanye","kanye west","mcgavock high school","Nashville","nashville sounds","rutherford county","tennessee","that is messed up","urban residents association"],"categories":["News"],"contentEncoded":"<div id=\"greet_block\"><noscript><div class=\"greet_block wpgb_cornered\"><div class=\"greet_text\"><div class=\"greet_image\"><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/feed/rss/\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/plugins/wp-greet-box/images/rss_icon.png\" alt=\"WP Greet Box icon\"></a></div>Hello there! If you&apos;re new to Nashvillest, you might want to <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/nashvillest\" rel=\"nofollow\"><strong>subscribe to our RSS feed</strong></a> to make sure you don&apos;t miss anything! We&apos;re also on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/nashvillest\" target=\"blank\"><strong>Twitter</strong></a> if you&apos;d like to join us there!<div style=\"clear:both\"></div><div class=\"greet_block_powered_by\">Powered by <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/projects/wordpress-plugins/wp-greet-box-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"WP Greet Box WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WP Greet Box</a> <a href=\"http://omninoggin.com/\" title=\"WordPress Plugin\" style=\"text-decoration:none;\">WordPress Plugin</a></div><div style=\"clear:both\"></div></div></div></noscript></div><p><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/05/1235208437_4d00403570.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-118\" title=\"1235208437_4d00403570\" src=\"http://nashvillest.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/05/1235208437_4d00403570.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"273\"></a></p><p>Good morning, Nashville. The season of high school graduations is upon us and what an eventful season it is, though not as joyous as you might think. A man with a <a href=\"http://www.wsmv.com/news/16325968/detail.html\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wsmv.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">loaded gun</a> was arrested outside of McGavock High School&#x2019;s graduation over the weekend, a Glencliff High School <a href=\"http://www.wkrn.com/global/story.asp?s=8345482\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wkrn.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">senior prank</a> ended in an arrest on Sunday night, and a Rutherford County teen was injured after <a href=\"http://www.wsmv.com/news/16333207/detail.html?rss=nash&amp;psp=news\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.wsmv.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">falling off</a> of the hood of a car during a graduation celebration yesterday. WKRN does bring us one happy story, though, where our new favorite Nashville blog <a href=\"http://www.thatismessedup.com\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.thatismessedup.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">That Is Messed Up</a> helped one crime-stopping high school senior <a href=\"http://thatismessedup.com/2008/05/19/graduation-denied/\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;thatismessedup.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">make it to his ceremony</a>. Local media, 1; juvenile court system, 0.</p><ul><li><strong>Comcastic</strong>. For the first time since it started in 2002, <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20080519/TUNEIN/80519056/-1/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Bonnaroo will be televised</a> nationwide on Fuse TV, which sucks for us because we don&#x2019;t get that channel Nashville unless we have satellite or digital cable. We really just want to see Kanye.</li><li><strong>But who will trim our hedges?</strong> Good news for Metro employees: Those 200 layoffs we promised earlier are <a href=\"http://www.nashvillecitypaper.com/news.php?viewStory=60319\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">down to 80</a> and still dropping, which means we may not lose our grass cutters after all. Whew.</li><li><strong>Bits &amp; Pieces</strong>. The Sounds are on a roll, <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20080519/SPORTS0401/80519106/-1/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">taking down Memphis</a> last night 7-3 &#x2026; East Nashville Farmer&#x2019;s Market <a href=\"http://www.tennessean.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20080519/FEATURES01/80519021/-1/RSS05\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.tennessean.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">opens</a> tomorrow &#x2026; More <a href=\"http://www.weather.com/weather/local/37215?lswe=37215&amp;lwsa=WeatherLocalUndeclared&amp;from=whatwhere\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.weather.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">beautiful weather</a> in store for Wednesday &#x2026; Urban Residents Association worried about <a href=\"http://www.nashvillecitypaper.com/news.php?viewStory=60331\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.nashvillecitypaper.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">more crime</a> downtown.</li></ul><p><em>Photo by <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/paulnich/1235208437/in/pool-nashvillest\" onclick=\"javascript:_gaq.push([&apos;_trackEvent&apos;,&apos;outbound-article&apos;,&apos;www.flickr.com&apos;]);\" target=\"_blank\">Paul Nicholson</a>.</em></p><p>Related posts:<ol><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2008/05/23/bright-early-schools-out-edition/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Bright &amp; Early: School&#x2019;s Out Edition\">Bright &amp; Early: School&#x2019;s Out Edition</a></li><li><a href=\"http://nashvillest.com/2008/06/16/bright-early-hug-a-sound-edition/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Permanent Link: Bright &amp; Early: Hug A Sound Edition\">Bright &amp; Early: Hug A Sound Edition</a></li></ol></p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<!--END .entry-content .article-->"}